cs.AR, cs.NI, cs.ET, cs.SY, cs.IT 

This paper discusses the development of Medium Access Control (MAC) strategies for Wireless Network-on-Chip (WNoC), which is a subfield of computer architecture and embedded systems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.AR (Computer Architecture), followed by cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) and cs.ET (Embedded Systems). The paper also discusses the performance objectives and traffic characteristics of on-chip communication, which could fall under cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.IT (Information Theory).
